# Hausmeister — Design System

A portable design spec for the **Hausmeister** brand: an absurd, slightly cursed
social app launching at Big Berlin Hack 2026. The vibe is **Berlin
techno-meets-bureaucracy**: a Kreuzberg lamppost poster crossed with a
passive-aggressive municipal notice. Dark mode only.

Drop this file into Claude Code as a reference (`/design.md` or paste into
context) when extending the product.

---

## 1. Brand & Voice

- **Name:** Hausmeister (with definite article: *Der Hausmeister*)
- **Tone:** dryly funny, passive-aggressive, bureaucratic, slightly unhinged.
  Mostly English with short German flavor words sprinkled in for texture
  (Regel, Komposthaufen, Hausordnung, Mülltonne, Treppenhaus, Aushang,
  Vorschrift, Schritt, Verfahren, Hausverwaltung).
- **Don't:** corporate SaaS copy, emoji-heavy hype, "we're so excited",
  cuteness, purple gradients, generic AI aesthetics.
- **Do:** stamps, file numbers (`Akte №047-K`), §-paragraphs, dotted-line
  signatures, "Effective immediately", "Logged and ignored".

---

## 2. Color Palette

All colors are authored in **OKLCH**. HEX values are approximations for
non-OKLCH tools — OKLCH is the source of truth.

### Core palette

| Token              | Role                          | OKLCH                         | ~HEX      |
|--------------------|-------------------------------|-------------------------------|-----------|
| `--ink`            | Background (near-black, green tint) | `oklch(0.16 0.012 110)` | `#1c1d17` |
| `--bone`           | Foreground / warm off-white   | `oklch(0.94 0.025 95)`        | `#f1ecd8` |
| `--olive`          | Primary / CTA                 | `oklch(0.62 0.13 115)`        | `#8a9a3d` |
| `--olive-deep`     | Primary shadow / deep accent  | `oklch(0.42 0.10 118)`        | `#56612a` |
| `--yellow-faded`   | Accent / stamps / Aushang     | `oklch(0.82 0.14 92)`         | `#dcc34a` |
| `--stamp-red`      | Destructive / warning stamp   | `oklch(0.55 0.22 28)`         | `#c54426` |

### Surfaces & text

| Token                 | Role                  | OKLCH                          | ~HEX      |
|-----------------------|-----------------------|--------------------------------|-----------|
| `--background`        | Page bg (= `--ink`)   | `oklch(0.16 0.012 110)`        | `#1c1d17` |
| `--foreground`        | Body text (= `--bone`)| `oklch(0.94 0.025 95)`         | `#f1ecd8` |
| `--card`              | Raised surface        | `oklch(0.20 0.014 110)`        | `#23241d` |
| `--popover`           | Popover surface       | `oklch(0.18 0.012 110)`        | `#1f201a` |
| `--muted`             | Subtle surface        | `oklch(0.24 0.012 110)`        | `#2a2b24` |
| `--muted-foreground`  | Secondary text        | `oklch(0.66 0.02 100)`         | `#a4a08a` |
| `--border`            | Hairlines             | `oklch(0.32 0.02 110)`         | `#3c3d33` |
| `--input`             | Form field bg         | `oklch(0.28 0.015 110)`        | `#33342c` |
| `--ring`              | Focus ring (= olive)  | `oklch(0.62 0.13 115)`         | `#8a9a3d` |

### Usage rules

- **Background is never pure black** — always the green-tinted `--ink`.
- **Body text is never pure white** — always warm `--bone`.
- **Olive = action.** Use only for primary CTAs, focus rings, key accents.
- **Faded yellow = official stamps, frames, hover state of CTA, highlights.**
- **Stamp red is rare** — destructive actions or one "warning" stamp per page max.
- **Never use ad-hoc hex/Tailwind classes** like `text-white`, `bg-zinc-900`.
  Always reference tokens.

---

## 3. Typography

Two Google Fonts, loaded together:

```css
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;700;800&family=Space+Grotesk:wght@400;500;700&display=swap');
```

| Family              | Use                                                        |
|---------------------|------------------------------------------------------------|
| **JetBrains Mono**  | Display headlines, stamps, labels, file numbers, all-caps  |
| **Space Grotesk**   | Long-form prose / fallback sans (rarely needed on landing) |

### Type roles

| Role             | Font            | Size (mobile → desktop) | Weight | Tracking         | Notes |
|------------------|-----------------|-------------------------|--------|------------------|-------|
| Hero `H1`        | JetBrains Mono  | `2.25rem` → `4.5rem`    | 800    | `-0.02em`        | line-height `0.95` |
| Section `H2`     | JetBrains Mono  | `1.875rem` → `3rem`     | 800    | `-0.02em`        |       |
| Card `H3`        | JetBrains Mono  | `1.25rem` → `1.5rem`    | 700    | `-0.01em`        |       |
| Body / mono prose| JetBrains Mono  | `0.875rem` → `1rem`     | 400    | normal           | use for nearly all body copy on landing |
| Stamp / label    | JetBrains Mono  | `0.625rem` → `0.75rem`  | 700    | `0.12em`, UPPER  | for "Aushang", section tags |
| Long-form sans   | Space Grotesk   | `1rem`                  | 400    | normal           | only for paragraph-heavy pages |

The mono-everywhere look is intentional: it reads like a printed municipal
notice. Don't soften it with friendly sans-serifs unless the page genuinely
needs long reading flow.

---

## 4. Spacing, Radius, Layout

- **Container:** `max-w-6xl` (≈1152px), `px-4`. Mobile-first.
- **Section padding:** `py-16` mobile, `py-20–24` desktop.
- **Radius:** **sharp.** Base radius is `0.125rem` (~2px). Buttons, cards,
  stamps are essentially square. Never use pill/`rounded-full` except for
  the status dot.
- **Borders:** 1px hairlines (`--border`) for structure; **2px solid**
  borders (olive or yellow-faded) for emphasis frames (Aushang, ticker).
- **Grid feel:** prefer `gap-px` between cards on a `bg-border` parent so
  you get crisp 1px dividers between cells.
- **Asymmetry:** small rotations (`rotate(-2deg)` for stamps, `rotate(1.5deg)`
  for the QR card) and offset shadows (`8px 8px 0 0 var(--olive-deep)`) for
  a printed-poster feel.

---

## 5. Texture & Atmosphere

Two layered effects on `body` create the "Kreuzberg lamppost" texture.

### Grunge specks (radial gradients)

```css
--grunge:
  radial-gradient(circle at 20% 30%, oklch(0.62 0.13 115 / 0.06) 0px, transparent 2px),
  radial-gradient(circle at 80% 70%, oklch(0.82 0.14 92 / 0.05) 0px, transparent 2px),
  radial-gradient(circle at 60% 20%, oklch(0.94 0.025 95 / 0.04) 0px, transparent 1px);
```

### Faint horizontal scan lines

```css
body {
  background-image:
    var(--grunge),
    repeating-linear-gradient(
      0deg,
      transparent 0px,
      transparent 3px,
      oklch(0 0 0 / 0.04) 3px,
      oklch(0 0 0 / 0.04) 4px
    );
  background-attachment: fixed;
}
```

### Hero scanline overlay

A `::before` pseudo-element with `mix-blend-mode: multiply` and 2px black
stripes — gives the hero a CRT/printed-paper feel.

```css
.scanline::before {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background: repeating-linear-gradient(
    180deg,
    transparent 0,
    transparent 2px,
    oklch(0 0 0 / 0.18) 2px,
    oklch(0 0 0 / 0.18) 3px
  );
  pointer-events: none;
  mix-blend-mode: multiply;
}
```

---

## 6. Components

### Stamp

Rotated, monospace, all-caps badge. Default ink is yellow; red variant for
warnings.

```css
.stamp {
  border: 2px solid currentColor;
  padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
  transform: rotate(-2deg);
  display: inline-block;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  font-weight: 700;
}
```

Examples: `Aushang · §1 BGB`, `Verfahren`, `Live · Komposthaufen`.

### Primary button (CTA)

- Olive background, ink text, **2px olive border**.
- **Square** (no border-radius beyond 2px).
- Hover: swap to faded yellow background + border.
- Mono, bold, uppercase, wide tracking.
- Right-arrow `→` glyph that nudges right on hover.

```html
<a class="
  inline-flex items-center gap-3
  bg-[var(--olive)] text-[var(--primary-foreground)]
  px-6 py-4
  font-mono text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest
  border-2 border-[var(--olive)]
  hover:bg-[var(--yellow-faded)] hover:border-[var(--yellow-faded)]
  transition-colors
">
  Talk to Der Hausmeister →
</a>
```

### Aushang frame (notice card)

- 2px `--yellow-faded` border, `--card` background.
- Tiny mono label sits *on top of* the border (negative `top` + bg-matched
  background to "cut" the border).
- Inner list uses dashed dividers between items.

### Ticker

- Full-bleed strip with `border-y-2 border-[var(--olive)]`.
- Items separated by olive `▌` glyph.
- CSS `@keyframes ticker { 0% { translateX(0) } 100% { translateX(-50%) } }`,
  duplicate the children once so the loop is seamless. Duration `40s` linear.

### Status dot

`h-2 w-2 bg-[var(--olive)]` with subtle `flicker` animation (4s ease-in-out,
opacity 1 → 0.85 → 1). Used in the top bar to suggest "system online".

### QR card

- `--bone` background, `p-4 sm:p-5`, `rotate(1.5deg)`.
- Hard offset shadow: `8px 8px 0 0 var(--olive-deep)`.
- QR `bgColor="#f1ecd8"`, `fgColor="#1a1a14"` for paper feel.
- Footer line: scan instruction + red file number on the right.

### Tag chips (hero meta)

Plain `border border-[var(--border)]`, `px-2 py-1`, mono `text-[10px]`,
muted-foreground color. Used for "passive-aggressive", "no signup, no email".

---

## 7. Motion

Minimal, mechanical, never bouncy.

| Animation     | Where               | Spec                                          |
|---------------|---------------------|-----------------------------------------------|
| `ticker`      | Komposthaufen strip | `40s linear infinite`, `translateX 0 → -50%`  |
| `flicker`     | Status dot          | `4s ease-in-out infinite`, opacity `1↔0.85`   |
| Button arrow  | Primary CTA hover   | `translateX(0 → 4px)`, `transition-transform` |
| Color swaps   | Hover states        | `transition-colors` (default duration)        |

No spring physics, no parallax, no scroll-triggered fades.

---

## 8. Iconography

Use **typographic glyphs**, not icon libraries.

- Steps: `✶`, `≈`, `☞`
- Section dividers: `§`, `№`, `·`
- Ticker bullet: `▌`
- Arrow: `→`

If a real icon is unavoidable, draw it as a 1.5px stroke monoline in
`--olive`, square corners.

---

## 9. Copy patterns

- Section tags: `Verfahren`, `Aushang`, `Hausordnung`, `Live · Komposthaufen`.
- File numbers: `Akte №047-K`, `v0.1-kompost`.
- Rules: `Regel §<number>: <English sentence with one German noun>.`
- Signatures: `Signed: D. Hausmeister` + `Berlin · DD.MM.2026`.
- Negative claims: `No signup. No newsletter. Just the Komposthaufen.`

---

## 10. Drop-in CSS (Tailwind v4 / native CSS variables)

Paste into `src/styles.css` (or equivalent). Works with Tailwind v4 `@theme`
or as plain CSS variables.

```css
@import "tailwindcss" source(none);
@source "../src";
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;700;800&family=Space+Grotesk:wght@400;500;700&display=swap');

@theme inline {
  --font-mono: "JetBrains Mono", ui-monospace, monospace;
  --font-sans: "Space Grotesk", system-ui, sans-serif;

  --color-background: var(--background);
  --color-foreground: var(--foreground);
  --color-card: var(--card);
  --color-popover: var(--popover);
  --color-primary: var(--primary);
  --color-primary-foreground: var(--primary-foreground);
  --color-secondary: var(--secondary);
  --color-muted: var(--muted);
  --color-muted-foreground: var(--muted-foreground);
  --color-accent: var(--accent);
  --color-destructive: var(--destructive);
  --color-border: var(--border);
  --color-input: var(--input);
  --color-ring: var(--ring);
}

:root {
  --radius: 0.125rem;

  /* Hausmeister palette */
  --background: oklch(0.16 0.012 110);   /* ink */
  --foreground: oklch(0.94 0.025 95);    /* bone */
  --card: oklch(0.20 0.014 110);
  --popover: oklch(0.18 0.012 110);
  --primary: oklch(0.62 0.13 115);       /* olive */
  --primary-foreground: oklch(0.14 0.01 110);
  --secondary: oklch(0.82 0.14 92);      /* faded yellow */
  --secondary-foreground: oklch(0.14 0.01 110);
  --muted: oklch(0.24 0.012 110);
  --muted-foreground: oklch(0.66 0.02 100);
  --accent: oklch(0.82 0.14 92);
  --accent-foreground: oklch(0.14 0.01 110);
  --destructive: oklch(0.55 0.22 28);    /* stamp red */
  --destructive-foreground: oklch(0.96 0.01 95);
  --border: oklch(0.32 0.02 110);
  --input: oklch(0.28 0.015 110);
  --ring: oklch(0.62 0.13 115);

  /* Brand aliases */
  --olive: oklch(0.62 0.13 115);
  --olive-deep: oklch(0.42 0.10 118);
  --yellow-faded: oklch(0.82 0.14 92);
  --bone: oklch(0.94 0.025 95);
  --ink: oklch(0.16 0.012 110);
  --stamp-red: oklch(0.55 0.22 28);

  /* Texture */
  --grunge:
    radial-gradient(circle at 20% 30%, oklch(0.62 0.13 115 / 0.06) 0px, transparent 2px),
    radial-gradient(circle at 80% 70%, oklch(0.82 0.14 92 / 0.05) 0px, transparent 2px),
    radial-gradient(circle at 60% 20%, oklch(0.94 0.025 95 / 0.04) 0px, transparent 1px);
}

@layer base {
  * { border-color: var(--border); }

  html, body {
    background-color: var(--background);
    color: var(--foreground);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  body {
    background-image:
      var(--grunge),
      repeating-linear-gradient(
        0deg,
        transparent 0px,
        transparent 3px,
        oklch(0 0 0 / 0.04) 3px,
        oklch(0 0 0 / 0.04) 4px
      );
    background-attachment: fixed;
  }
}

@layer utilities {
  .font-display {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  .font-stamp {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .text-olive { color: var(--olive); }
  .text-yellow-faded { color: var(--yellow-faded); }
  .text-bone { color: var(--bone); }
  .bg-olive { background-color: var(--olive); }
  .bg-yellow-faded { background-color: var(--yellow-faded); }
  .border-olive { border-color: var(--olive); }
  .border-yellow-faded { border-color: var(--yellow-faded); }

  .stamp {
    border: 2px solid currentColor;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
    transform: rotate(-2deg);
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .scanline::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: repeating-linear-gradient(
      180deg,
      transparent 0,
      transparent 2px,
      oklch(0 0 0 / 0.18) 2px,
      oklch(0 0 0 / 0.18) 3px
    );
    pointer-events: none;
    mix-blend-mode: multiply;
  }

  @keyframes ticker {
    0% { transform: translateX(0); }
    100% { transform: translateX(-50%); }
  }
  .animate-ticker { animation: ticker 40s linear infinite; }

  @keyframes flicker {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
    50% { opacity: 0.85; }
  }
  .animate-flicker { animation: flicker 4s ease-in-out infinite; }
}
```

